posts.raw_content:
Hey guys, idk how to say this but yeah.. 
My wife was diagnosed with breast cancer on December 8th. It’s HER2+(HR-), stage II-a. She had her first chemo Wednesday January 7th so treatment is underway. It’s aggressive treatment, but the outlook is good.
I haven’t shared sooner because we’ve been processing and I didn’t really know how to say it. But I needed you guys to know what’s going on. No pressure on saying the right thing and we don’t need anything right now. I just wanted you all in the loop with us.

Wanted to send this to my buddies in real life but I could never bring myself to do it. It's sat drafted in a small group text thread for a week. Just needed to say it, even it's into the void.

We are Highschool sweethearts. Celebrating 20 years together and 10 years married this year. I love her so much and it's so scary to see her scared. I have kept it together. I will keep it together. Thanks for listening.

posts.raw_content:
Hey guys, idk how to say this but yeah.. 
My wife was diagnosed with breast cancer on December 8th. It’s HER2+(HR-), stage II-a. She had her first chemo Wednesday January 7th so treatment is underway. It’s aggressive treatment, but the outlook is good.
I haven’t shared sooner because we’ve been processing and I didn’t really know how to say it. But I needed you guys to know what’s going on. No pressure on saying the right thing and we don’t need anything right now. I just wanted you all in the loop with us.

Wanted to send this to my buddies in real life but I could never bring myself to do it. It's sat drafted in a small group text thread for a week. Just needed to say it, even it's into the void.

We are Highschool sweethearts. Celebrating 20 years together and 10 years married this year. I love her so much and it's so scary to see her scared. I have kept it together. I will keep it together. Thanks for listening.
